aVNow, a bit of economic history, I think, may be helpful here.
p43
aVAround 1850, one of the biggest U.S. industries was whaling.
p44
aVAnd whale oil lit practically every building.
p45
aVBut in the nine years before Drake struck oil, in 1859,
p46
aVat least five-sixths of that whale oil-illuminating market disappeared,
p47
aVthanks to fatal competitors, chiefly oil and gas made from coal,
p48
aVto which the whalers had not been paying attention.
p49
aVSo, very unexpectedly, they ran out of customers
p50
aVbefore they ran out of whales.
p51
aVThe remnant whale populations were saved by technological innovators
p52
aVand profit-maximizing capitalists.
p53
aa(lp54
